be allowed to pass into Nazi hands".

13
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,810
But my work is not yet completed.

14
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,380
The tests that you have made were
good enough to show its possibilities.

15
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:11,416
Isn't that understating it? If it's successful,
it will revolutionize defensive warfare.

16
00:04:11,517 --> 00:04:15,180
And it is a revolution that we do not wish
to have brought about by the Third Reich.

17
00:04:15,288 --> 00:04:18,416
- Then I am to leave the country.
- As soon as the Nazi invasion starts.

18
00:04:18,524 --> 00:04:20,719
I have here passports for
yourself and your daughter.

19
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:23,625
Arrangements have been made for you to
carry on your work in another country.

20
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:25,698
Where, you will be told when the time comes.

21
00:04:25,798 --> 00:04:27,766
I have made out lists...

22
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:30,335
<i>[Droning In Distance]</i>

23
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:34,807
<i>[Airplanes Approaching]</i>

24
00:04:46,185 --> 00:04:48,153
Ours?

25
00:04:49,188 --> 00:04:51,179
No. Theirs.

26
00:05:01,534 --> 00:05:05,766
If we resist German protection,
Prague will be bombed.

27
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:09,908
<i>[Man] Rrotection. Rrotection from what?</i>

28
00:05:10,009 --> 00:05:13,103
Give me a direct line to the
Ministry of the Interior, at once!

29
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:18,382
What?

30
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:22,388
The minister left 10 minutes ago
for the Central Radio Station.

31
00:05:25,391 --> 00:05:29,350
[Man On Radio] The German command
has given the order to march.

32
00:05:29,462 --> 00:05:34,923
At this moment, Nazi troops are
streaming across our frontiers.

33
00:05:35,034 --> 00:05:37,662
In our present defenseless condition...

34
00:05:37,770 --> 00:05:40,238
resistance is worse than useless.

35
00:05:41,274 --> 00:05:43,640
Citizens of Czechoslovakia...

36
00:05:43,743 --> 00:05:46,940
we must bear the trials that lie ahead...

37
00:05:47,046 --> 00:05:50,641
<i>with fortitude and courage.</i>

38
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,911
<i>Be of good heart.</i>

39
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:55,044
<i>And remember-</i>

40
00:05:55,154 --> 00:05:58,123
<i>long live Czechoslovakial</i>

41
00:06:18,945 --> 00:06:21,243
But will the British
government give me facilities?

42
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:23,815
Everything is arranged.
You will be met at Croydon.

43
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:26,214
Here are the details. Now,
you haven't a minute to lose.

44
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:30,619
The plane leaves the airfield in
half an hour, and it will be the last.

45
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:33,453
- But, uh, will you be there?
- I must stay.

46
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,823
Axel, your daughter.

47
00:06:37,363 --> 00:06:40,355
Is that you, Anna? You have heard?

48
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:44,903
Listen, dear. I don't want to alarm you,
but we have to leave the country at once.

49
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:46,904
Go to the airport.

50
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:48,974
I will be waiting for you.

51
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,635
Immediately. Do you understand?

52
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:54,611
Yes. Yes, at once. Where are we going?

53
00:06:56,149 --> 00:06:58,049
England?

54
00:06:58,151 --> 00:06:59,618
Yes, of course.

55
00:06:59,719 --> 00:07:02,017
- What's happening, Miss Anna?
- Martha, I've got to leave at once.

56
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:04,248
Help me put some things in a bag.

57
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:32,547
Anna Bomasch, you are under arrest.

58
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:38,651
[Engines Idling]

59
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:46,165
- We cannot wait any longer!
- Please, another moment!

60
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:48,165
My daughter was leaving at once.

61
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:51,395
But the city's occupied already. We must go!

62
00:07:56,809 --> 00:07:58,709
Away! Come on!

63
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:10,884
<i>Schnelll Schnelll</i>

64
00:08:16,262 --> 00:08:18,162
[Mutters]

65
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:30,133
<i>[Shouts Order In German]</i>

66
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:32,643
[German]

67
00:08:32,745 --> 00:08:34,645
<i>Marsch.</i>

68
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:42,077
<i>[Soldier Continues Shouting Orders]</i>

69
00:08:46,259 --> 00:08:48,284
<i>Marschl</i>

70
00:08:48,394 --> 00:08:50,089
<i>Aufschliessenl</i>

71
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:54,833
Halt!

72
00:08:54,934 --> 00:08:56,834
Turn right.

73
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,838
Edward Klein, for laziness.

74
00:08:59,939 --> 00:09:02,134
